idth":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"e0f7f2fe-a304-daa3-3ee7-b507ed67b56e","name":"Note: Stamp & Shape Email"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Payload Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.messageId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Classify with AI · ②→ Record Rejected Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"f6598a27-0145-713c-fe5e-d1bf4936867e","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"4469046f-c254-e02b-00d7-770e526fa4c4","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Classify with AI\n\nLLM classification into: Action Needed, Reference, Ignore (+fallback). Output port order matches this list.\n\nPorts: ①→ Store as Action Needed · ②→ Store as Reference, Capture Failure Context · ③→ Store as Ignore · ④→ Alert Slack — Other\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"99be668a-43e8-0369-fe96-e74e32290d9b","name":"Note: Classify with AI"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Classify with AI** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1090],"id":"ac7f2a80-eca9-9f41-cf99-f77eb68836fb","name":"Note: OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Action Needed\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,40],"id":"16dc45e9-5501-8967-f3b9-4d233de1cf53","name":"Note: Store as Action Needed"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Reference\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,490],"id":"669e9cee-8bde-0f6a-5408-d22bdbf7b224","name":"Note: Store as Reference"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Ignore\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1857,940],"id":"5d85c7a2-1b79-5c6e-63ef-ef287907ec24","name":"Note: Store as Ignore"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Alert Slack — Other\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2181,1390],"id":"4deca067-b2ea-4eb5-2cb6-97cf270eb92e","name":"Note: Alert Slack — Other"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reunite Branches\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2829,520],"id":"48ed27c1-4791-dcbc-f236-71c6cd75496b","name":"Note: Reunite Branches"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 50 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Sort Emails Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"7e0e7ade-705f-97c5-95f2-bd6a0e1f3255","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Emails Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"b69b0e90-278c-c64e-d12c-1d4f5b7054d1","name":"Note: Sort Emails Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"d226ab39-ba13-6edd-adbc-40c0103bc611","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"b30d7da6-b027-3260-6309-5058724c498b","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"ca0f9854-55e4-a7ea-c523-ef0beb23a476","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,1540],"id":"5720aea6-ba0d-f23f-1fb6-6ea1d2d45ea8","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,1540],"id":"d6e2b528-057b-2494-63fd-dd0455ed4e97","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Distill long emails with Notion and Telegram\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nDistill long emails with Notion and Telegram. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual newsletters is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Stamp & Shape Email → Payload Valid? → Classify with AI → Store as Action Needed → Reunite Branches → Cap Batch Volume → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating newsletters in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Notion integration token; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"7ff0529d-3746-2a3e-c564-5e89f664503c","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"e7f085d6-5107-f773-1d59-d5b18e6a1fa3","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"a8e31cfa-e495-1b45-0ba8-e5ddd4db946b","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"bb45569b-dc1c-0d80-d703-2c19101b5df4","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your newsletters process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-500],"id":"58b64f1a-4e5b-dcde-c911-0944c696e5d2","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Email","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Email":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenAI Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Classify with AI":{"main":[[{"node":"Store as Action Needed","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Reference","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Ignore","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Alert Slack — Other","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Action Needed":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Reference":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Ignore":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Alert Slack — Other":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":3}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Reunite Branches":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Emails Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Emails Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"08a6b814-339d-4e6d-99b5-fddf4d8dda29","id":"FDX02170"}